You&#39;ll need to proxy your API calls to the appropriate endpoint during development. I assume relative urls will be fine on deployment, correct? Or you will be using absolute urls there instead.

To proxy all you need is a proxy configuration file that you pass to the ng server command:

proxy.conf.json

     {
      &quot;/api/*&quot;: {
        &quot;target&quot;: &quot;http://localhost:8080&quot;,
        &quot;secure&quot;: false,    
        &quot;changeOrigin&quot;: true
      }

In this case any call made to /api/* will be proxied to localhost:8080. If your back-end is not mapped to /api/ you cna add a rewrite rule:

    {
          &quot;/api/*&quot;: {
            &quot;target&quot;: &quot;http://localhost:8080&quot;,
            &quot;secure&quot;: false,    
            &quot;changeOrigin&quot;: true,
            &quot;pathRewrite&quot;: {
               &quot;^/api&quot;: &quot;&quot;
             }
          }

